    "path": "src/host/executor",
    "name": "executor",
    "purpose": "Executor folder module for host-side tool execution. executor.rs defines Executor, whose new(agent_tx) stores the shared agent SessionMessage sender alongside a ToolRegistry and an empty WorkQueue of active ExecutionRuntime records keyed by ExeId, and exposes route_session_event and preview. create_execution resolves the requested tool via registry.get by request.signature.name and builds ExecutionRuntime::new(tool, request, agent_tx.clone()). tool.rs defines the Executor-side Tool handle to an external tool executable; input_schema() and output_schema() keep returning String by cloning the typed preview schema content fields. The execution child module implements the per-execution runtime that reads ExecutionRequest.input.content.",
    "changeStatus": "modified"
  },
  "childModules": [
    {
      "path": "src/host/executor/execution",
      "name": "execution",
      "purpose": "Per-execution host runtime split out of executor.rs: ExecutionRuntime drives one agent Execution, spawning a worker in new that reads raw tool input from parameters.input.content on the typed ExecutionRequest, runs tool.execute, and emits ExecutionUpdate plus terminal ExecutionStatus while handling Cancel/Kill control events; ExecutionContext holds the host-local Tool handle, ExecutionRequest, and agent SessionMessage sender."
